<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFramework>netstandard2.0</TargetFramework>
    <Authors>A Name Not Yet Taken AB</Authors>
    <Company>A Name Not Yet Taken AB</Company>
    <Product>a-fortnox-client</Product>
    <Description>This library is a client to the Fortnox Api (www.fortnox.se), the library can be used to connect to the Fortnox Api and to call methods in the Fortnox Api.</Description>
    <Copyright>Copyright Â© 2017</Copyright>
    <PackageIconUrl>http://www.annytab.com/annytab_logo_512x512.png</PackageIconUrl>
    <PackageTags>ASP.NET, .NET, Core, C#, Fortnox, Api, Client, SDK</PackageTags>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>I have removed IFortnoxRepository and created typed http clients instead. Errors are now returned from methods, not logged in the method as before. The caller can decide what to do with the error information. I have also added more fields to models.

+ FortnoxClient includes a http client and is used to call methods in the Fortnox Api.
+ FortnoxAuthorizationClient includes a http client and is used to get an access token.</PackageReleaseNotes>
    <NeutralLanguage>English</NeutralLanguage>
    <GeneratePackageOnBuild>true</GeneratePackageOnBuild>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/annytab/a-fortnox-client</PackageProjectUrl>
    <PackageLicenseUrl>https://github.com/annytab/a-fortnox-client/blob/master/LICENSE</PackageLicenseUrl>
    <Version>1.0.4</Version>
    <LangVersion>latest</LangVersion>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.Extensions.Logging" Version="2.1.1" />
    <PackageReference Include="Newtonsoft.Json" Version="11.0.2" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
